<subSubSection pageId="32" pageNumber="233" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="32.[151,1437,151,1760]" pageId="32" pageNumber="233">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,314,151,176]" pageId="32" pageNumber="233">Diagnosis</emphasis>
: 
<taxonomicName authority="Wesener, 2019" authorityName="Wesener" authorityYear="2019" box="[329,486,152,176]" class="Diplopoda" family="Zephronidae" genus="Sphaerobelum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sphaerotheriida" pageId="32" pageNumber="233" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="splendidum" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis box="[329,486,152,176]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="233">S. splendidum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[493,557,151,176]" pageId="32" pageNumber="233">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[493,557,151,176]" pageId="32" pageNumber="233" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
belongs to a group of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Verhoeff" authorityYear="1924" box="[810,971,152,176]" class="Diplopoda" family="Zephronidae" genus="Sphaerobelum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sphaerotheriida" pageId="32" pageNumber="233" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[810,971,152,176]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="233">Sphaerobelum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species in which the mesal margin of the femur is unmodified (
<figureCitation box="[396,499,188,213]" captionStart="FIGURE 22" captionStartId="33.[151,250,1922,1944]" captionTargetBox="[168,1421,193,1901]" captionTargetId="figure@33.[166,1421,193,1901]" captionTargetPageId="33" captionText="FIGURE 22. Sphaerobelum splendidum n. sp., holotype (SMF); A: coxa of first left leg with first stigmatic plate; B: 9th left leg; C: coxa of second left leg with gonopore; D: left anterior telopod, anterior view; E: left anterior telopod, posterior view; F: left anterior telopod, lateral view; G: right posterior telopod, anterior view; H: right posterior telopod, posterior view. Abbreviations: Cx = coxa; St-Pl = stigmatic plate; Syn-Cx = syncoxite. Scale bars = 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2601119/files/figure.png" pageId="32" pageNumber="233">Fig. 22B</figureCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName authority="Wesener, 2019" authorityName="Wesener" authorityYear="2019" box="[518,676,188,212]" class="Diplopoda" family="Zephronidae" genus="Sphaerobelum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sphaerotheriida" pageId="32" pageNumber="233" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="splendidum" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis box="[518,676,188,212]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="233">S. splendidum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[683,747,188,213]" pageId="32" pageNumber="233">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[683,747,188,213]" pageId="32" pageNumber="233" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
shares only with 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Verhoeff" authorityYear="1924" box="[945,1074,188,212]" class="Diplopoda" family="Zephronidae" genus="Sphaerobelum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sphaerotheriida" pageId="32" pageNumber="233" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hirsutum">
<emphasis box="[945,1074,188,212]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="233">S. hirsutum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Verhoeff" authorityYear="1924" box="[1087,1242,188,212]" class="Diplopoda" family="Zephronidae" genus="Sphaerobelum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sphaerotheriida" pageId="32" pageNumber="233" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="clavigerum">
<emphasis box="[1087,1242,188,212]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="233">S. clavigerum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Wesener, 2019" authorityName="Wesener" authorityYear="2019" box="[1256,1364,188,212]" class="Diplopoda" family="Zephronidae" genus="Sphaerobelum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sphaerotheriida" pageId="32" pageNumber="233" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigrum" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis box="[1256,1364,188,212]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="233">S. nigrum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1372,1436,188,213]" pageId="32" pageNumber="233">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1372,1436,188,213]" pageId="32" pageNumber="233" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Wesener, 2019" authorityName="Wesener" authorityYear="2019" box="[198,389,224,248]" class="Diplopoda" family="Zephronidae" genus="Sphaerobelum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sphaerotheriida" pageId="32" pageNumber="233" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="schwendingeri" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis box="[198,389,224,248]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="233">S. schwendingeri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[396,458,223,248]" pageId="32" pageNumber="233">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[396,458,223,248]" pageId="32" pageNumber="233" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
the presence of a &quot;hook&quot; at telopoditomere 4 of the posterior telopods (
<figureCitation box="[1257,1396,223,248]" captionStart="FIGURE 22" captionStartId="33.[151,250,1922,1944]" captionTargetBox="[168,1421,193,1901]" captionTargetId="figure@33.[166,1421,193,1901]" captionTargetPageId="33" captionText="FIGURE 22. Sphaerobelum splendidum n. sp., holotype (SMF); A: coxa of first left leg with first stigmatic plate; B: 9th left leg; C: coxa of second left leg with gonopore; D: left anterior telopod, anterior view; E: left anterior telopod, posterior view; F: left anterior telopod, lateral view; G: right posterior telopod, anterior view; H: right posterior telopod, posterior view. Abbreviations: Cx = coxa; St-Pl = stigmatic plate; Syn-Cx = syncoxite. Scale bars = 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2601119/files/figure.png" pageId="32" pageNumber="233">Figs 22G, H</figureCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName authority="Wesener, 2019" authorityName="Wesener" authorityYear="2019" class="Diplopoda" family="Zephronidae" genus="Sphaerobelum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sphaerotheriida" pageId="32" pageNumber="233" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="splendidum" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="233">S. splendidum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[287,351,260,285]" pageId="32" pageNumber="233">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[287,351,260,285]" pageId="32" pageNumber="233" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
differs from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Verhoeff" authorityYear="1924" box="[500,629,260,284]" class="Diplopoda" family="Zephronidae" genus="Sphaerobelum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sphaerotheriida" pageId="32" pageNumber="233" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hirsutum">
<emphasis box="[500,629,260,284]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="233">S. hirsutum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the presence of glabrous tergites, from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Verhoeff" authorityYear="1924" box="[1105,1259,260,284]" class="Diplopoda" family="Zephronidae" genus="Sphaerobelum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sphaerotheriida" pageId="32" pageNumber="233" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="clavigerum">
<emphasis box="[1105,1259,260,284]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="233">S. clavigerum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the presence of a short locking carina on the anal shield. Differs from 
<taxonomicName authority="Wesener, 2019" authorityName="Wesener" authorityYear="2019" box="[852,967,296,319]" class="Diplopoda" family="Zephronidae" genus="Sphaerobelum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sphaerotheriida" pageId="32" pageNumber="233" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigrum" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis box="[852,967,296,319]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="233">S. nigrum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[980,1049,295,320]" pageId="32" pageNumber="233">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[980,1049,295,320]" pageId="32" pageNumber="233" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
in the presence of a cylindrical antennomere 6, the presence of only 5–7 ventral spines on the tarsi (8–10 ventral spines in the aother species) (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURE 22" captionStartId="33.[151,250,1922,1944]" captionTargetBox="[168,1421,193,1901]" captionTargetId="figure@33.[166,1421,193,1901]" captionTargetPageId="33" captionText="FIGURE 22. Sphaerobelum splendidum n. sp., holotype (SMF); A: coxa of first left leg with first stigmatic plate; B: 9th left leg; C: coxa of second left leg with gonopore; D: left anterior telopod, anterior view; E: left anterior telopod, posterior view; F: left anterior telopod, lateral view; G: right posterior telopod, anterior view; H: right posterior telopod, posterior view. Abbreviations: Cx = coxa; St-Pl = stigmatic plate; Syn-Cx = syncoxite. Scale bars = 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2601119/files/figure.png" pageId="32" pageNumber="233">Fig. 22B</figureCitation>
), and the presence of a strongly curved telopoditomere 4 of the posterior telopod, all characters only shared with 
<taxonomicName authority="Wesener, 2019" authorityName="Wesener" authorityYear="2019" box="[213,344,404,428]" class="Diplopoda" family="Zephronidae" genus="Sphaerobelum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sphaerotheriida" pageId="32" pageNumber="233" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="laoticum" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis box="[213,344,404,428]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="233">S. laoticum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[356,424,404,429]" pageId="32" pageNumber="233">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[356,424,404,429]" pageId="32" pageNumber="233" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Wesener, 2019" authorityName="Wesener" authorityYear="2019" box="[489,685,404,428]" class="Diplopoda" family="Zephronidae" genus="Sphaerobelum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sphaerotheriida" pageId="32" pageNumber="233" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="schwendingeri" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis box="[489,685,404,428]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="233">S. schwendingeri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[698,766,404,429]" pageId="32" pageNumber="233">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[698,766,404,429]" pageId="32" pageNumber="233" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Wesener, 2019" authorityName="Wesener" authorityYear="2019" box="[778,941,404,428]" class="Diplopoda" family="Zephronidae" genus="Sphaerobelum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sphaerotheriida" pageId="32" pageNumber="233" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="splendidum" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis box="[778,941,404,428]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="233">S. splendidum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[953,1020,404,429]" pageId="32" pageNumber="233">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[953,1020,404,429]" pageId="32" pageNumber="233" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
differs from both in the following characters: Anterior telopod, telopoditomeres 3 and 4 clearly separated (
<figureCitation box="[954,1037,439,464]" captionStart="FIGURE 22" captionStartId="33.[151,250,1922,1944]" captionTargetBox="[168,1421,193,1901]" captionTargetId="figure@33.[166,1421,193,1901]" captionTargetPageId="33" captionText="FIGURE 22. Sphaerobelum splendidum n. sp., holotype (SMF); A: coxa of first left leg with first stigmatic plate; B: 9th left leg; C: coxa of second left leg with gonopore; D: left anterior telopod, anterior view; E: left anterior telopod, posterior view; F: left anterior telopod, lateral view; G: right posterior telopod, anterior view; H: right posterior telopod, posterior view. Abbreviations: Cx = coxa; St-Pl = stigmatic plate; Syn-Cx = syncoxite. Scale bars = 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2601119/files/figure.png" pageId="32" pageNumber="233">Figs 22</figureCitation>
D–F) (separation only partly visible in 
<taxonomicName authority="Wesener, 2019" authorityName="Wesener" authorityYear="2019" box="[181,308,476,500]" class="Diplopoda" family="Zephronidae" genus="Sphaerobelum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sphaerotheriida" pageId="32" pageNumber="233" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="laoticum" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis box="[181,308,476,500]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="233">S. laoticum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[316,380,476,501]" pageId="32" pageNumber="233">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[316,380,476,501]" pageId="32" pageNumber="233" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Wesener, 2019" authorityName="Wesener" authorityYear="2019" box="[437,630,476,500]" class="Diplopoda" family="Zephronidae" genus="Sphaerobelum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sphaerotheriida" pageId="32" pageNumber="233" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="schwendingeri" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis box="[437,630,476,500]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="233">S. schwendingeri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[638,702,476,501]" pageId="32" pageNumber="233">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[638,702,476,501]" pageId="32" pageNumber="233" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
), antennae and legs brown (both red in 
<taxonomicName authority="Wesener, 2019" authorityName="Wesener" authorityYear="2019" box="[1158,1286,476,500]" class="Diplopoda" family="Zephronidae" genus="Sphaerobelum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sphaerotheriida" pageId="32" pageNumber="233" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="laoticum" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis box="[1158,1286,476,500]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="233">S. laoticum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1294,1358,476,501]" pageId="32" pageNumber="233">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1294,1358,476,501]" pageId="32" pageNumber="233" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Wesener, 2019" authorityName="Wesener" authorityYear="2019" class="Diplopoda" family="Zephronidae" genus="Sphaerobelum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sphaerotheriida" pageId="32" pageNumber="233" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="schwendingeri" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="233">S. schwendingeri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[321,384,511,536]" pageId="32" pageNumber="233">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[321,384,511,536]" pageId="32" pageNumber="233" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="32" pageNumber="233" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="32.[151,1437,151,1760]" pageId="32" pageNumber="233">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,534,548,573]" pageId="32" pageNumber="233">Description: Measurements</emphasis>
: Body length 
<quantity box="[710,819,548,572]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.1399999999999997" pageId="32" pageNumber="233" unit="mm" value="21.4">21.4 mm</quantity>
. Width, of thoracic shield = 
<quantity box="[1170,1275,548,572]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.13" pageId="32" pageNumber="233" unit="mm" value="11.3">11.3 mm</quantity>
(= broadest). Height, of thoracic shield = 
<quantity box="[463,549,583,608]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.9" pageId="32" pageNumber="233" unit="mm" value="5.9">5.9 mm</quantity>
(= highest). 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[691,820,583,608]" pageId="32" pageNumber="233">Coloration</emphasis>
: Head and collum chestnut brown. Tergites black olive green, posterior tergite margin light brown (
<figureCitation box="[643,733,620,645]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="11.[151,250,1916,1938]" captionTargetBox="[150,1423,987,1897]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[150,1436,983,1903]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURE 6. Habitus multi-layer stacked photographs of Sphaerobelum species. A: Sphaerobelum bolavensis n. sp.; B: Sphaerobelum phouloei n. sp.; C: Sphaerobelum denticulatum n. sp.; D: Sphaerobelum spinatum n. sp.; E: Sphaerobelum lachneeis n. sp.; F: Sphaerobelum peterjaegeri n. sp.; G: Sphaerobelum nigrum n. sp.; H: Sphaerobelum splendidum n. sp.; I: Sphaerobelum laoticum n. sp. Not to scale." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2601084/files/figure.png" pageId="32" pageNumber="233">Fig. 6H</figureCitation>
). Antennae and legs dirty brown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="32.[151,1437,151,1760]" pageId="32" pageNumber="233">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,263,655,680]" pageId="32" pageNumber="233">Head</emphasis>
: with 40–50 ocelli. Antennae extending posteriorly to leg 5. Size of antennomeres 1=2=3=4=5&lt;6, 6th apically widened, not flat. Apical disc carrying 49/46 apical cones. Antennomere 1–5 with only few setae. Organ of Tömösváry located inside antennal groove. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[672,879,727,752]" pageId="32" pageNumber="233">Gnathochilarium</emphasis>
: usual for the order, sensory cones located in clusters. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[250,376,764,789]" pageId="32" pageNumber="233">Mandibles</emphasis>
: not investigated.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="32.[151,1437,151,1760]" pageId="32" pageNumber="233">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,437,799,824]" pageId="32" pageNumber="233">First stigmatic plate</emphasis>
: small, well-rounded, inconspicuous (
<figureCitation box="[863,967,799,824]" captionStart="FIGURE 22" captionStartId="33.[151,250,1922,1944]" captionTargetBox="[168,1421,193,1901]" captionTargetId="figure@33.[166,1421,193,1901]" captionTargetPageId="33" captionText="FIGURE 22. Sphaerobelum splendidum n. sp., holotype (SMF); A: coxa of first left leg with first stigmatic plate; B: 9th left leg; C: coxa of second left leg with gonopore; D: left anterior telopod, anterior view; E: left anterior telopod, posterior view; F: left anterior telopod, lateral view; G: right posterior telopod, anterior view; H: right posterior telopod, posterior view. Abbreviations: Cx = coxa; St-Pl = stigmatic plate; Syn-Cx = syncoxite. Scale bars = 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2601119/files/figure.png" pageId="32" pageNumber="233">Fig. 22A</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[985,1154,799,824]" pageId="32" pageNumber="233">Laterotergites</emphasis>
: 1 and 2 with a short, but sharp, spine-like projection. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[470,558,836,861]" pageId="32" pageNumber="233">Collum</emphasis>
: only short setae at margin.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="32.[151,1437,151,1760]" pageId="32" pageNumber="233">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,385,871,896]" pageId="32" pageNumber="233">Thoracic shield</emphasis>
: Shallow grooves with few setae, surface glabrous. Margin towards grooves with 2 anterior and 3 or 4 posterior keels. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[468,563,908,933]" pageId="32" pageNumber="233">Tergites</emphasis>
: shiny, polished, at high magnification chagrinated. Paratergite tips weakly projecting posteriorly (
<figureCitation box="[412,503,943,968]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="11.[151,250,1916,1938]" captionTargetBox="[150,1423,987,1897]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[150,1436,983,1903]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURE 6. Habitus multi-layer stacked photographs of Sphaerobelum species. A: Sphaerobelum bolavensis n. sp.; B: Sphaerobelum phouloei n. sp.; C: Sphaerobelum denticulatum n. sp.; D: Sphaerobelum spinatum n. sp.; E: Sphaerobelum lachneeis n. sp.; F: Sphaerobelum peterjaegeri n. sp.; G: Sphaerobelum nigrum n. sp.; H: Sphaerobelum splendidum n. sp.; I: Sphaerobelum laoticum n. sp. Not to scale." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2601084/files/figure.png" pageId="32" pageNumber="233">Fig. 6H</figureCitation>
). Tergite surface glabrous except for paratergite grooves. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1163,1313,943,968]" pageId="32" pageNumber="233">Endotergum</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[1331,1423,943,968]" captionStart="FIGURE 9" captionStartId="13.[151,250,1423,1445]" captionTargetBox="[152,1434,1021,1400]" captionTargetId="figure@13.[152,1435,1021,1402]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURE 9. Endoterga of the body ring 9 of different Sphaerobelum species. A: Sphaerobelum bolavensis n. sp.; B: Sphaerobelum phouloei n. sp.; C: Sphaerobelum spinatum n. sp.; D: Sphaerobelum splendidum n. sp. Abbreviations: cp = cuticular patterns; iA = inner area." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2601090/files/figure.png" pageId="32" pageNumber="233">Fig. 9D</figureCitation>
): inner section without setae or spines. Single, sparse row of slightly elliptical large cuticular impressions, distance between impressions slightly larger than their diameter. Externally 2–3 rows of medium length marginal bristles, protruding at most up to tergite margin (
<figureCitation box="[598,687,1052,1077]" captionStart="FIGURE 9" captionStartId="13.[151,250,1423,1445]" captionTargetBox="[152,1434,1021,1400]" captionTargetId="figure@13.[152,1435,1021,1402]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURE 9. Endoterga of the body ring 9 of different Sphaerobelum species. A: Sphaerobelum bolavensis n. sp.; B: Sphaerobelum phouloei n. sp.; C: Sphaerobelum spinatum n. sp.; D: Sphaerobelum splendidum n. sp. Abbreviations: cp = cuticular patterns; iA = inner area." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2601090/files/figure.png" pageId="32" pageNumber="233">Fig. 9D</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[707,763,1052,1077]" pageId="32" pageNumber="233">Legs</emphasis>
: leg-pair 1 with 2 ventral spines, leg pair 2 with 3, leg pair 3 with 4 or 5, leg pairs 4–21 with only 5–7. Apical spine present at tarsi 3–21. In leg 9, femur 1.6 times, tarsus 3.3 times longer than wide (
<figureCitation box="[438,545,1124,1149]" captionStart="FIGURE 22" captionStartId="33.[151,250,1922,1944]" captionTargetBox="[168,1421,193,1901]" captionTargetId="figure@33.[166,1421,193,1901]" captionTargetPageId="33" captionText="FIGURE 22. Sphaerobelum splendidum n. sp., holotype (SMF); A: coxa of first left leg with first stigmatic plate; B: 9th left leg; C: coxa of second left leg with gonopore; D: left anterior telopod, anterior view; E: left anterior telopod, posterior view; F: left anterior telopod, lateral view; G: right posterior telopod, anterior view; H: right posterior telopod, posterior view. Abbreviations: Cx = coxa; St-Pl = stigmatic plate; Syn-Cx = syncoxite. Scale bars = 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2601119/files/figure.png" pageId="32" pageNumber="233">Fig. 22B</figureCitation>
). Coxae 1 and 2 without a coxal process (
<figureCitation box="[1048,1197,1124,1149]" captionStart="FIGURE 22" captionStartId="33.[151,250,1922,1944]" captionTargetBox="[168,1421,193,1901]" captionTargetId="figure@33.[166,1421,193,1901]" captionTargetPageId="33" captionText="FIGURE 22. Sphaerobelum splendidum n. sp., holotype (SMF); A: coxa of first left leg with first stigmatic plate; B: 9th left leg; C: coxa of second left leg with gonopore; D: left anterior telopod, anterior view; E: left anterior telopod, posterior view; F: left anterior telopod, lateral view; G: right posterior telopod, anterior view; H: right posterior telopod, posterior view. Abbreviations: Cx = coxa; St-Pl = stigmatic plate; Syn-Cx = syncoxite. Scale bars = 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2601119/files/figure.png" pageId="32" pageNumber="233">Figs 22A, C</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1221,1360,1124,1149]" pageId="32" pageNumber="233">Anal shield</emphasis>
: wellrounded, glabrous, underside with a single very small, almost dot-like, locking carina.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="32.[151,1437,151,1760]" pageId="32" pageNumber="233">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,479,1196,1221]" pageId="32" pageNumber="233">Male sexual characters</emphasis>
: Male gonopore large, covered by small, inconspicuous plate (
<figureCitation box="[1204,1310,1196,1221]" captionStart="FIGURE 22" captionStartId="33.[151,250,1922,1944]" captionTargetBox="[168,1421,193,1901]" captionTargetId="figure@33.[166,1421,193,1901]" captionTargetPageId="33" captionText="FIGURE 22. Sphaerobelum splendidum n. sp., holotype (SMF); A: coxa of first left leg with first stigmatic plate; B: 9th left leg; C: coxa of second left leg with gonopore; D: left anterior telopod, anterior view; E: left anterior telopod, posterior view; F: left anterior telopod, lateral view; G: right posterior telopod, anterior view; H: right posterior telopod, posterior view. Abbreviations: Cx = coxa; St-Pl = stigmatic plate; Syn-Cx = syncoxite. Scale bars = 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2601119/files/figure.png" pageId="32" pageNumber="233">Fig. 22C</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="233">Anterior telopods</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[272,365,1231,1256]" captionStart="FIGURE 22" captionStartId="33.[151,250,1922,1944]" captionTargetBox="[168,1421,193,1901]" captionTargetId="figure@33.[166,1421,193,1901]" captionTargetPageId="33" captionText="FIGURE 22. Sphaerobelum splendidum n. sp., holotype (SMF); A: coxa of first left leg with first stigmatic plate; B: 9th left leg; C: coxa of second left leg with gonopore; D: left anterior telopod, anterior view; E: left anterior telopod, posterior view; F: left anterior telopod, lateral view; G: right posterior telopod, anterior view; H: right posterior telopod, posterior view. Abbreviations: Cx = coxa; St-Pl = stigmatic plate; Syn-Cx = syncoxite. Scale bars = 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2601119/files/figure.png" pageId="32" pageNumber="233">Figs 22</figureCitation>
D–F): telopoditomere 1 rectangular, as long as wide. Telopoditomere 2 large, as long as telopoditomeres 3 and 4 combined. Process of telopoditomere 2 located posteriorly and laterally, visible in anterior view. Process of telopoditomere 2 slender, projecting almost as high as apical part of telopoditomere 4, apical part well-rounded. Telopoditomere 3 as long as wide, almost twice as long as telopoditomere 4, inconspicuous. telopoditomere 3 and 4 fused in posterior view, divided by a suture in anterior and lateral views. Telopoditomere 4 well-rounded, tapering apically. Posterior aspect with one black sclerotized spot and 2 spines. All podomeres apically covered with long setae. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[532,751,1447,1472]" pageId="32" pageNumber="233">Posterior telopods</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[766,908,1447,1472]" captionStart="FIGURE 22" captionStartId="33.[151,250,1922,1944]" captionTargetBox="[168,1421,193,1901]" captionTargetId="figure@33.[166,1421,193,1901]" captionTargetPageId="33" captionText="FIGURE 22. Sphaerobelum splendidum n. sp., holotype (SMF); A: coxa of first left leg with first stigmatic plate; B: 9th left leg; C: coxa of second left leg with gonopore; D: left anterior telopod, anterior view; E: left anterior telopod, posterior view; F: left anterior telopod, lateral view; G: right posterior telopod, anterior view; H: right posterior telopod, posterior view. Abbreviations: Cx = coxa; St-Pl = stigmatic plate; Syn-Cx = syncoxite. Scale bars = 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2601119/files/figure.png" pageId="32" pageNumber="233">Figs 22G, H</figureCitation>
): telopoditomere 1 elongated, twice as long as wide. Immovable finger (process of telopoditomere 2) as long as movable finger, consisting of telopoditomeres 3 and 4. Immovable finger with a characteristic, distally swollen apex, massively swollen and curved towards movable finger. Apically broader than base. Telopoditomere 3 elongated, towards immovable finger at midpoint with a triangular extension carrying two large spines. Telopoditomere 4 tapering, apically strongly curved towards immovable finger, with thinly projecting apex. At inner margin with a large spine at midpoint and 1 or 2 smaller spines apically. Entire telopoditomere 1 and 2 at both sides covered with long setae, except for the immovable finger. Telopoditomere 3 only baso-laterally with a few setae, remaining part as well as telopoditomere 4 glabrous.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[199,1308,1735,1760]" pageId="32" pageNumber="233" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="32.[151,1437,151,1760]" box="[199,1308,1735,1760]" pageId="32" pageNumber="233">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,413,1735,1760]" pageId="32" pageNumber="233">Derivatio nominis</emphasis>
: splendidum, noun in apposition, based on the shiny appearance of this species.
</paragraph>
